    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.50"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">84 Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">50</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">MID-WEST SILVER LAKE
                        <lb/>
                    WRITERS' CONFERENCE</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    Oak Haven, Route Three
                        <lb/>
                    Fairmont, Minnesota
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>November 8 1958</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Doctor Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>By now you should have one of our souvenir Oak Haven spoons. Our custom is to give one to each leader.</p>
                
                <p>Plans for next summer's conference are well underway. Some of the leaders have been selected. Our fourth cabin is well under way, it is under roof and will be ready by next summer.</p>
                
                <p>You have shown a wonderful interest in what is under way here. I hope you will be pleased at the following idea. We want you as a visitor next summer at our Conference. We are arranging for a painter-artist or a photographer to make a fine portrait of you for our permanent memento. You will be paid for your transportation here and back home. Of course full hospitality, and you may stay one or all four days with us. The Conference date i<del>n</del><add>s</add> Augsust 19-22 (4 days).</p>
                
                <p>We begin advertising in the magazines in January and wish include your name as a visiting poet.</p>
                
                <p>Besides your good letter we have received several very complimentary letters about our 1958 Conference, all of which is most encouraging.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Believe me,</salute>
                
                    <salute>Most gratefully yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>P Evans Coleman</signed>
                    
                    <signed>P Evans Coleman, Ph D</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
